                <h1>Understanding the History of HIV: A Comprehensive Overview</h1>
                <p>The history of HIV dates back to the early 1980s when the virus was first identified, linked to severe immune deficiencies. Originating from simian immunodeficiency virus (SIV), it crossed to humans in Central Africa. The epidemic sparked global health initiatives, awareness campaigns, and significant advancements in antiretroviral treatments.</p>
